statement.title: Problem Description
statement.content: On a two-dimensional plane, give you n integer points. Your task is to figure out how many different regular polygon these points can make.

statement.title: Input
statement.content: The input file consists of several test cases. Each case the first line is a numbers N (N <= 500). The next N lines ,each line contain two number Xi and Yi(-100 <= xi,yi <= 100), means the points’ position.(the data assures no two points share the same position.)

statement.title: Output
statement.content: For each case, output a number means how many different regular polygon these points can make.
